author: Upper Echelon
description:
With a newly released, alleged competitor to Wikipedia emerging, (Grokipedia) and a realization that Grokipedia is merely a tweaked and politically twisted version of Wikipedia to begin with, its important to start talking about what happens to a world where information repositories are restructured in a way where facts ONLY care about readers feelings.

It is absolutely imperative that we maintain a shared reality where truth is truth, instead of highly manipulated and re-scraped imitations of the largest human made encyclopedia in history. Even when we agree with some of those restructured descriptions.
